rates using a time-weighted average of the premium between perpetual and spot prices over the 8-hour period. The exchange applies a ±0.05% dampening mechanism to prevent excessive rates during high volatility. Funding payments are automatically deducted from traders' futures wallets, with long positions paying shorts when rates are positive and vice versa. Bitget's funding rate formula incorporates both interest rate differential and premium components, typically resulting in rates between -0.75% to +0.75% daily."}]]}],"$Lf",["$L10","$L11","$L12"],"$L13"]}],"$L14"]}]]}]
